data.text: COVID-19 affects us all, but most especially vulnerable populations such as refugees
and migrants. To assess the public health and social impact of the COVID-19
pandemic on refugees and migrants, WHO and partners are conducting a global study
called ‘ApartTogether’. You can participate through a survey currently being conducted.
To combat misconceptions about COVID-19 in Nigeria, WHO and the Nigerian
government are scaling up strategies to demystify COVID-19 by working with traditional
leaders. The aim is to empower traditional leaders, who command great respect, to
